ABTMSE
  • Reference
  • Articles

An S4 class object that contains all Operating Model Inputs in the format for M3 operating model estimation

Name
The name of the operating model input
Date
The date and time the object was created
Author
Who made the object
Notes
Anything noteworthy
PrimarySource
The primary origins of these data
nsim
The number of simulations
npop
number of stocks (e.g. 2, East-West)
nages
number of ages (e.g. 18: 1-17 and 18+)
nyears
number of years of simulation by statistical catch at length
nHyears
number of historical years for stock reduction analysis prior ot statistical catch at length
nsubyears
number of subyears (e.g. 4 quarters)
nareas
number of areas
proyears
number of projection years for closed-loop MSE analysis
nlen
number of length classes
lenbins
vector of length bins that define length classes
interval
how often (number of years) assessments/MPs are implemented (e.g. interval=3 means 2015 assessment, 2016-2017 no assessment, 2018 assessment etc)
nma
number of movement age classes
ma
an array of movement age classes [npop x nage]
Rectype
a matrix specifying the recruitment type (a stock can have multiple types of recruitment over the projected time period) by stock [type, stock]
h
a vector nstocks long specifying the steepness of the B-H stock recruitment curve (currently unused)
recgrad
a matrix specifying a possible future gradient in recruitment expressed as a per cent per year [stock x 2 (upper / lower)]
Recind
an array specifyign which historical recruitment type to use in each projected year [nsim x nstock x projection year]
Recpars
an array of stock recruitment parameters by recruitment type [nsim x nstock x rectype (Hockey stock / B-H) x 2 (h or jointpoint/R0)]
Reccv
a vector nstock long of recruitment variability by stock
AC
a vector nstock long of recruitment autocorrelation
Recsubyr
a vector nstock long specifying which subyear recruitment occurs in
Linfmu
a vector nstock long specifying the mean maximum length of individuals
Kmu
a vector nstock long specifying the mean growth parameter K
t0
a vector nstock long specifying the theoretical age at length zero
a
a vector nstock long, the weight-length parameter a W=aL^b
b
a vector nstock long, the weight-length parameter b W=aL^b
Len_age
an array of length at age by stock [stock x age]
Wt_age
an array of weight at age by stock [stock x age]
ageM
an array of maturity at age by stock [stock x age]
D
current stock depletion by stock (currently unused)
Size_area
a vector nareas long, the relative size of each area
mov
a very large array storing simulated movement by stock [sim x stock x age x subyear x from area x to area]
nfleets
the number of fishing fleets
iALK
an array representing the inverse age-length key (conditional probability of length given age) [sim x stock x year x age x length class]
hZ
an array of historical mortality rate estimates [stock, year, subyear, age, area]
HCobs
an array of historical catch observations [year, subyear, age, area]
Cobs
an array of catch observations [year, subyear, area, fleet]
E
an array of standardized effort (partial effort)[sim, fleet, year, subyear, area]
qE
a vector nfleets long, the catchability of the fleets
qI
a vector nI long of catchabilities by fishery independent index
qCPUE
a vector nCPUE long of catchabilities by fishery CPUE index
sel
an array of selectivities [sim, fleets, length class]
selpars
array of selectivity parameters (currently unused)
mat
array of maturity [sim, stock, age, year]
M
array of natural mortality rate [sim, stock, age, year]
Recdevs
of historical recruitment deviations [sim, stock, year]
R0
vector nstock long of unfished recruitment (currently unused - recpars)
muR
a vector nstock long of mean recruitment
MSY
a matrix of MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
BMSY
a matrix of Biomass at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
VBMSY
a matrix of vulnerable Biomass at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
SSBMSY
a matrix of spawning biomass at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
FMSY
a matrix of fishing exploitation rate at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
UMSY
a matrix of fishing harvest rate at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
FMSYa
a matrix of apical (coresponding with age that is most vulnerable) fishing exploitation rate at MSY values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
SSBMSY_SSB0
a matrix of spawning biomass at MSY relative to unfished, values per simulation and stock [sim x stock]
nydist
the number of years used to determine equilibrium spatial distribution
Snames
a vector nstock long naming each stock
area_defs
a list of area definitions for graphing (lons and lats describing the polygon)
areanams
a character vector of area names
seed
a random seed for generation of simulations to ensure reproducibility
